{"TopicId":188352,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Is there a Facility Upgrade Tree?","CreatedByName":"GungaDin","CreatedById":92717,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-19T13:40:16Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"GungaDin","CreatedById":92717,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-19T13:40:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m in career mode and need to get to the point where I can learn to navigate and dock but I think my Kerbils don\u0027r have the ability to \u0027lock\u0027 on a target.\u00A0 I also would like them to be able to take soil samples from different biomes.\u00A0 Is there a guide somewhere to tell me which facilities to upgrade to gain these skills? I see the Science tree just fine but the facility upgrade path is less clear.\u00A0 Thanks.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-19T13:46:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis should tell you everything you need about the building upgrades.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Kerbal_Space_Center\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Kerbal_Space_Center\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever, that won\u0027t help your kerbal pilots lock onto their target, they\u0027ll need to level up for that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Specialization\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Specialization\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Experience\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Experience\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"VoidSquid","CreatedById":196199,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-19T13:48:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom the Wiki:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ch1 lang=\u0022en\u0022 style=\u0022border-bottom:1px solid #a2a9b1;color:#000000;font-size:1.8em;padding:0px;\u0022 xml:lang=\u0022en\u0022\u003E\nPilot\n\u003C/h1\u003E\n\u003Ctable style=\u0022background-color:#f8f9fa;border-collapse:collapse;border:1px solid #a2a9b1;color:#000000;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Ctbody\u003E\u003Ctr\u003E\u003Cth style=\u0022background-color:#eaecf0;border:1px solid #a2a9b1;padding:.2em .4em;text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\nLevel\n\u003C/th\u003E\n\u003Cth style=\u0022background-color:#eaecf0;border:1px solid #a2a9b1;padding:.2em .4em;text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\nEffects provided\n\u003C/th\u003E\n\u003Cth style=\u0022background-color:#eaecf0;border:1px solid #a2a9b1;padding:.2em .4em;text-align:center;\u0022\u003E\nG Tolerance\n\u003C/th\u003E\n\u003C/tr\u003E\u003Ctr\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0022border:1px solid #a2a9b1;padding:.2em .4em;\u0022\u003E\n\u2606\u2606\u2606\u2606\u2606\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd style=\u0022border:1px solid #a2a9b1;padding:.2em .4em;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E and Stability\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd style=\u0022border:1px solid #a2a9b1;padding:.2em .4em;\u0022\u003E\n1.15x\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003C/tr\u003E\u003Ctr\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0022border:1px solid #a2a9b1;padding:.2em .4em;\u0022\u003E\n\u2605\u2606\u2606\u2606\u2606\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd style=\u0022border:1px solid #a2a9b1;padding:.2em .4em;\u0022\u003E\nLock towards prograde and retrograde\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd style=\u0022border:1px solid #a2a9b1;padding:.2em .4em;\u0022\u003E\n1.3x\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003C/tr\u003E\u003Ctr\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0022border:1px solid #a2a9b1;padding:.2em .4em;\u0022\u003E\n\u2605\u2605\u2606\u2606\u2606\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd style=\u0022border:1px solid #a2a9b1;padding:.2em .4em;\u0022\u003E\nLock towards normal and anti-normal, radial and anti-radial\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd style=\u0022border:1px solid #a2a9b1;padding:.2em .4em;\u0022\u003E\n1.45x\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003C/tr\u003E\u003Ctr\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0022border:1px solid #a2a9b1;padding:.2em .4em;\u0022\u003E\n\u2605\u2605\u2605\u2606\u2606\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd style=\u0022border:1px solid #a2a9b1;padding:.2em .4em;\u0022\u003E\nLock towards target, away from target, and towards maneuver\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd style=\u0022border:1px solid #a2a9b1;padding:.2em .4em;\u0022\u003E\n1.6x\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003C/tr\u003E\u003Ctr\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0022border:1px solid #a2a9b1;padding:.2em .4em;\u0022\u003E\n\u2605\u2605\u2605\u2605\u2606\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd style=\u0022border:1px solid #a2a9b1;padding:.2em .4em;\u0022\u003E\nNone\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd style=\u0022border:1px solid #a2a9b1;padding:.2em .4em;\u0022\u003E\n1.85x\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003C/tr\u003E\u003Ctr\u003E\u003Ctd style=\u0022border:1px solid #a2a9b1;padding:.2em .4em;\u0022\u003E\n\u2605\u2605\u2605\u2605\u2605\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd style=\u0022border:1px solid #a2a9b1;padding:.2em .4em;\u0022\u003E\nNone\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003Ctd style=\u0022border:1px solid #a2a9b1;padding:.2em .4em;\u0022\u003E\n2x\n\u003C/td\u003E\n\u003C/tr\u003E\u003C/tbody\u003E\u003C/table\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Pilot\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Pilot\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EUpgrading the\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Astronaut_Complex\u0022 style=\u0022color:#0b0080;font-size:14px;\u0022 title=\u0022Astronaut Complex\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EAstronaut Complex\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Eand\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Research_and_Development\u0022 style=\u0022color:#0b0080;font-size:14px;\u0022 title=\u0022Research and Development\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EResearch and Development\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Efacility allow taking\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/EVA_Report\u0022 style=\u0022color:#0b0080;font-size:14px;\u0022 title=\u0022EVA Report\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EEVA Reports\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003Eand\u003Cspan\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Surface_Sample\u0022 style=\u0022color:#0b0080;font-size:14px;\u0022 title=\u0022Surface Sample\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ESurface Samples\u003C/a\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#222222;font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E.\u0022\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Career\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Career\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-19T15:12:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe best you can do for figuring out the advantages of upgrading the facilities is to right click to open the Facility window (in \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E view), and then hover your mouse over the \u0022upgrade\u0022 button. It will tell you what advantages you get -- or you can look in the wiki as Geonovast said. However, the wiki has an error when it comes to the Tracking Station. To get visible orbits, vessel targeting,\u00A0and maneuver nodes, you need to upgrade the Tracking Station to level 2. And another error when it comes to R\u0026amp;D:\u00A0you need to upgrade it to Level 3 to get Surface Samples.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"k00b","CreatedById":196331,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-19T21:02:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn \u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Career\u0022 title=\u0022Career\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003ECareer\u003C/a\u003E mode, Surface Samples cannot be taken without having the \u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Research_and_Development\u0022 title=\u0022Research and Development\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EResearch and Development\u003C/a\u003E Facility and \u003Ca href=\u0022https://wiki.kerbalspaceprogram.com/wiki/Astronaut_Complex\u0022 title=\u0022Astronaut Complex\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EAstronaut Complex\u003C/a\u003E upgraded to second level.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Fraktal","CreatedById":184990,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-19T23:10:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223674541\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022188352\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568905934\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154251\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022bewing\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, bewing said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHowever, the wiki has an error when it comes to the Tracking Station. To get visible orbits, vessel targeting,\u00A0and maneuver nodes, you need to upgrade the Tracking Station to level 2.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo you don\u0027t need to upgrade the Mission Control as well?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-09-20T00:14:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223674804\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022188352\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221568934603\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184990\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Fraktal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Fraktal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo you don\u0027t need to upgrade the Mission Control as well?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes, Mission Control too, to Level 2. But the wiki has that part correct.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}